The gateway is a raw delegatecall dispatcher with dozens of route implementations sharing one storage context. I’m reading the gateway/controllers/base abstractions first, then drilling into bridge and swap modules where user-controlled calldata meets token approvals and external calls.
Audit plan focused on distinct exploit paths rather than exhaustive file-by-file notes.
  → Read core gateway, controller, and base route abstractions to map trust boundaries and shared storage assumptions
  • Trace swap modules for arbitrary external call, recipient, approval, and balance-accounting issues
  • Trace bridge modules for arbitrary recipients, stuck-funds, msg.value mismatches, nonce/refund misuse, and unsafe approvals
  • Consolidate only distinct reportable findings into the required JSON schema with precise locations
